      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:74:2",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/74/2",
      "text": [
        " «لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ وَ رُبَّمَا فَعَلْتُهُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2825 - Abdullah ibn Sinan asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a man who arrives for Hajj and finds the heat unbearable, so he performs Tawaf around the Ka'bah but delays the Sa’y until it cools down.\nAbu Abdullah (as) replied: \"There is no harm in doing so, and I have sometimes done it myself.\""
        ]
      }
    },
